Content Registry Microservice — Project Context (Memory Graph)
1. Project Objective
A FastAPI-based backend microservice designed for uploading educational content (images/PDFs), classifying it by metadata (Class, Subject, Chapter), and extracting text and math formulas (LaTeX) using pix2text. The system stores this metadata and extracted content in a local SQLite database, preparing it for future agent-based knowledge graph integration.

2. Technology Stack
Backend Framework: FastAPI with Uvicorn (local) / Gunicorn (production)
Database: SQLite (sqlite3) with WAL mode enabled.
Data Validation: Pydantic v2
OCR & Math Extraction: pix2text (used as a Mathpix alternative)
PDF Processing: PyMuPDF (fitz) — used for page-by-page PDF extraction with progress tracking
Storage: Local file system (uploads/ directory) and local DB (data/ directory).
3. Core API Endpoints
Upload & Extract
POST /api/content/upload: Uploads a file, stores metadata, auto-triggers full extraction in background.
POST /api/content/upload-extract: SSE (Server-Sent Events) — uploads AND extracts in a single call with live streaming progress. Returns events like:
data: {"percent": 42, "message": "Extracting page 3/7...", "status": "processing"}
data: {"percent": 100, "message": "Extraction complete", "status": "completed", "content_id": "...", "extracted_text": "..."}
GET /api/content/{id}/progress: Poll extraction progress for background extractions. Returns {"percent": 0-100, "message": "...", "status": "processing|completed|failed|pending"}.
Content CRUD
GET /api/content: Lists uploaded content with optional query filters (class_name, subject, chapter, search).
GET /api/content/{id}: Get a single content item with its extracted_text.
GET /api/content/{id}/download: Download the original file.
DELETE /api/content/{id}: Delete content + file.
GET /api/content/{id}/render: Renders extracted markdown as HTML with MathJax.
Metadata
GET /api/metadata/classes, /subjects, /chapters: Retrieve available filter options.
4. Extraction Architecture
Page-by-Page PDF Processing (with real progress)
PDFs are NOT processed as a single blob. Instead:

PyMuPDF (fitz) opens the PDF and counts total pages.
Each page is rendered to an image at 200 DPI.
pix2text.recognize_page() processes each page image individually.
A progress_cb(percent, message) callback fires after each page → enables real-time progress.
All page results are joined with --- separators.
Image paths are rewritten to public URLs via BASE_URL.
Image Extraction (with staged progress)
Images go through: Loading model (2%) → Preparing image (10%) → OCR (20%) → Saving (85%) → URL rewrite (95%) → Done (100%).

Progress Tracking
In-memory dict (_progress) protected by threading.Lock().
Works because Gunicorn runs 1 worker (single process).
GET /{id}/progress reads from this dict, with DB fallback if extraction already finished.
SSE Streaming (/upload-extract)
Uses threading.Thread + queue.Queue pattern.
Extraction runs in a background thread, pushes events to the queue.
FastAPI StreamingResponse reads from the queue and yields SSE events.
Keep-alive comments (: keepalive) sent every 0.5s to prevent connection drops.
5. Pix2Text Implementation Details
Transformers Bug: Pinned transformers>=4.35.0,<4.58.0 due to optimum-onnx bug.
Image Downscaling: Automatically resizes images larger than 1500px using PIL.
Markdown Output: Uses permanent asset directories under UPLOADS_DIR/extracted_assets/ (not temp dirs).
Path Rewriting: _rewrite_paths_to_urls() replaces local filesystem paths with BASE_URL/uploads/... URLs.